.TH NHOPKG.CONF 5 "@RELEASEDATE@" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "Nhopkg Manual"
.SH NAME
nhopkg.conf \- configuration file for the nhopkg package manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.I /etc/nhopkg/nhopkg.conf
.br
.I /usr/share/nhopkg/nhopkg.conf
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B nhopkg.conf
file defines the default behavior of the
.B nhopkg
universal package manager. It is read at startup unless overridden by command-line options.
.PP
If
.I /etc/nhopkg/nhopkg.conf
does not exist, nhopkg falls back to the system-provided default at
.I /usr/share/nhopkg/nhopkg.conf
.
.SH FILE FORMAT
The file uses standard Bash syntax. Each line sets a shell variable. Comments start with
.B #
.
.SH CONFIGURATION VARIABLES
.SS [Main paths]
These variables define the core directories used by nhopkg.

.TP
.B NHOPKG_LOCALSTATEDIR
Directory for nhopkg runtime data (packages, files, logs, cache).  
Default:
.I /var/lib/nhopkg

.TP
.B NHOPKG_BUILDIR
Base directory for building source packages.  
Default:
.I /usr/src/nhopkg

.TP
.B NHOPKG_LOCKFILE
Path to the lock file that prevents concurrent nhopkg instances.  
Default:
.I /var/lock/nhopkg

.TP
.B TMPDIR
Temporary directory for general use.  
Default:
.I /tmp

.TP
.B TEMPLATE_TMPDIR
Template for temporary directories created by nhopkg.  
Default:
.I .nhopkg.XXXXXXXXXX

.SS [Repository]
.TP
.B NHOPKG_REPO
URL of the default remote repository used by
.BR -S ", " --super-install .
.br
Default value is set at build time (e.g.,
.I https://repo.example.com
).

.SS [Behavior options]
.TP
.B NHOPKG_CHECKDEPS
Enable dependency resolution and installation.  
Values:
.I yes
(default) or
.I no

.TP
.B NHOPKG_PURGE
When removing a package, also remove packages that depend on it.  
Values:
.I no
(default) or
.I yes

.TP
.B NHOPKG_CHECKSHA256
Verify SHA256 checksums of packages.  
Values:
.I yes
(default) or
.I no

.TP
.B NHOPKG_CHECKARCH
Reject packages with incompatible architecture.  
Values:
.I yes
(default) or
.I no

.TP
.B VERBOSE_MODE
Enable verbose output during operations.  
Values:
.I no
(default) or
.I yes

.TP
.B NHOPKG_GETTEXT
Enable internationalization (i18n) via gettext.  
Values:
.I yes
(default) or
.I no

.SS [File tracking (for .srcnho builds)]
.TP
.B FIND_DIRS
Space-separated list of directories scanned to detect files installed by a source package.  
Default:
.I "/bin /boot /etc /lib /opt /sbin /srv /usr"

.TP
.B NOUPGRADE_FILES
Files that should never be overwritten during package upgrades (e.g., auto-generated caches).  
Default includes:
.RS
.nf
mimeinfo.cache
info/dir
info/dir.old
/etc/ld.so.cache
${NHOPKG_BUILDIR}
/etc/mtab
/etc/fstab
.fi
.RE

.SS [Database]
.TP
.B NHOPKG_DB
Path to the locate-style database used for dependency resolution.  
Default:
.I /var/lib/nhopkg/nhopkg.db

.TP
.B NO_DIRS_IN_DB
Directories excluded from the nhopkg database (for performance and security).  
Default:
.RS
.nf
/dev /home /media /mnt /opt /proc /run /sys /tmp \\
/usr/src /usr/share/zoneinfo /var
.fi
.RE

.SS [Localization]
.TP
.B TEXTDOMAIN
Gettext domain name (should not be modified).  
Default:
.I nhopkg

.TP
.B TEXTDOMAINDIR
Directory containing translation files (.mo).  
Default:
.I /usr/share/locale

.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
# Main paths
NHOPKG_LOCALSTATEDIR="/var/lib/nhopkg"
NHOPKG_BUILDIR="/usr/src/nhopkg"
NHOPKG_LOCKFILE="/var/lock/nhopkg"

# Repository
NHOPKG_REPO="https://packages.nhopkg.org/repo"

# Behavior
NHOPKG_CHECKDEPS="yes"
NHOPKG_CHECKSHA256="yes"
NHOPKG_CHECKARCH="yes"
VERBOSE_MODE="no"
NHOPKG_GETTEXT="yes"

# File tracking
FIND_DIRS="/bin /sbin /usr /etc /opt"
NOUPGRADE_FILES="/etc/ld.so.cache /var/cache/fontconfig"

# Database
NHOPKG_DB="/var/lib/nhopkg/nhopkg.db"
NO_DIRS_IN_DB="/tmp /proc /sys /dev /home"
.fi

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/nhopkg/nhopkg.conf
User-editable configuration file (takes precedence).
.TP
.I /usr/share/nhopkg/nhopkg.conf
Fallback default configuration (installed by nhopkg itself).

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nhopkg (8),
.BR updatedb (1),
.BR gettext (1)

